## 4. Slack – Short summary ONLY to Tester (DM) and #ai-report – NEVER to anyone else

**Three Slack paths (canonical index):** **`Cursor-Project/config/template/Slack_reporting_paths.md`**. **Path 1** — bug validation (Rule 32): unchanged. **Path 2** — **HandsOff:** **short** Slack via **`Slack_report_summary_short_template.md`** (includes path to **`Cursor-Project/config/playwright/Playwright_run_detailed_report_template.md`**). **Path 3** — scoped Slack: same short Slack + detailed file under **Chat reports**. Optional **long** Slack body: **`Slack_report_template.md`** only if the user explicitly requests it.

- **Problem:** Slack messages were too long; detailed TC mapping and links belong in the **file**, not in chat.
- **Rule (template):** Slack **text** MUST follow **`Slack_report_summary_short_template.md`** — **three blocks only** (title, Jira metadata, Total); optional **Notes:**. **MANDATORY file delivery:** **Upload** (1) **`{JIRA_KEY}.md`** and (2) **`playwright-report-detailed.md`** (when generated) as **Slack file attachments** with **`upload-file-to-slack.ps1`** to Tester + #ai-report (`C0AK96S1D7X`) whenever **`SLACK_API_TOKEN`** or **`SLACK_BOT_TOKEN`** is available — **#ai-report** is the **report channel** for these files. Do **not** replace files with long chat paste. Do **not** put per-test rows in chat unless the user explicitly asks for **`Slack_report_template.md`** long paste.
- **Rule (ONLY two recipients – CRITICAL):** The **short summary** must be sent **only** to (1) the **Tester** (DM) and (2) the **#ai-report** channel. **Do NOT send to Assignee or to any other Slack user.** When both apply, send the **same** short message to Tester and to **#ai-report** via `slack_send_message(channel_id: "C0AK96S1D7X", message: …)`. **Always use** **`C0AK96S1D7X`** for #ai-report. If no Tester in Jira, send only to #ai-report. If length limit applies, preserve header and totals; **do not** rely on pasting disk paths instead of **file uploads** when the upload script can run.
- **Tester from Jira – correct field only:** Always resolve the **Tester** from the ticket’s **"Tester"** custom field. In this project that is **`customfield_10095`** (single user picker). Use that user’s **displayName** for Slack. **Do NOT use** Assignee or **customfield_11151** (BA – Business Analyst). If `customfield_10095` is null, there is no Tester; send only to #ai-report.
- **Find Tester on Slack by name:** Call **`slack_search_users(query: <tester display name>)`** with the display name from **customfield_10095**; use the returned **User ID** as `channel_id` for the DM. Do **not** use hardcoded Slack user IDs; do **not** add @mention. Send the **same short summary** **only** to that Tester (DM) and #ai-report (**C0AK96S1D7X**). **Never send to Assignee or anyone else.**

Reference: `Slack_reporting_paths.md`; `Slack_report_summary_short_template.md`; `Slack_report_template.md` (optional long); `.cursor/commands/hands-off.md` Step 7; user-slack MCP.

