## Summary checklist (HandsOff)

- [ ] **Swagger refresh (Rule SWAGGER.0):** `update-swagger-specs.ps1` was executed in this session; every endpoint was grepped in the refreshed spec; every DTO schema was resolved; every payload field name, enum value, and type was cross-validated against the spec. The Swagger spec is the single source of truth — NOT the test case .md.
- [ ] Test cases: written to `test_cases/Backend/<Topic_name>.md` (TC-BE-N only) and `test_cases/Frontend/<Topic_name>.md` (TC-FE-N only); both files verified on disk; test_cases/README.md, Backend/README.md, and Frontend/README.md updated.
- [ ] **Precondition completeness (DRY):** Full entity-creation chain in `## Test data (preconditions)` once; each TC's `Preconditions:` references a slice + deltas only; no duplicated `POST /` lines across TCs; every entity described with endpoint and parameters (never just "entity exists"); full chain from Customer → POD → Product → Terms → Price component → Contract → Energy data → Billing run → Invoice → Payment etc.; dates and amounts included when they affect the outcome.
- [ ] **TC quality validation (Step 1.5):** test-case-quality-validator invoked after generation (STRICT 0-100 scoring); all TCs scored **≥80/100** on rubric (`Cursor-Project/docs/test_case_quality_rubric.md`); rewrite iterations completed (max 3); if still failing after 3, workflow blocked and escalated to user.
- [ ] Playwright: spec created in `EnergoTS/tests/cursor/{JIRA_KEY}-*.spec.ts` (or equivalent); file verified on disk; **number of `test()` blocks equals total number of test cases (TC-BE-N from Backend file + TC-FE-N from Frontend file)** – full coverage, 1:1.
- [ ] **Playwright precondition data creation (CRITICAL):** Spec uses **helper functions** (at file top) for shared preconditions called within each test via `test.step('Precondition: ...')`. **NO `test.beforeAll()` for preconditions.** NO tests query existing data, use hardcoded IDs, or assume entities exist. Entity creation follows dependency order: Terms → Price components → Products → Customers → PODs → Contracts → etc. Test-specific data created inline.
- [ ] **Validation (Step 4.5):** playwright-test-validator invoked; if failed, re-run test-case-generator and/or energo-ts-test and re-validate until pass or max iterations; only then run tests.
- [ ] Report: per **`Cursor-Project/config/playwright/Playwright_run_detailed_report_template.md`** filled — per test: TC mapping, links/ids, expected vs actual, meets expectation; if validation had issues, short Validation subsection.
- [ ] Slack (**path 2**): **three-block** text + **mandatory file uploads** of **`{JIRA_KEY}.md`** **and** **`playwright-report-detailed.md`** (when `playwright-report.json` existed) via **`upload-file-to-slack.ps1`** to Tester + **#ai-report** (`C0AK96S1D7X`) when token exists; never Assignee. Long Slack paste only if user explicitly asked (`Slack_report_template.md`).
- [ ] Agent questions: after report, collect questions from each participating agent (as needed); each question tagged with agent name; send questions after the report to the same recipients (Tester and #ai-report only).
- [ ] **Rule DPR.0:** Ran **`generate-detailed-report.mjs`** when JSON existed; uploaded **`playwright-report-detailed.md`** to **#ai-report** and Tester with the smart report (**`.cursor/rules/workflows/playwright_detailed_reporting.mdc`**).

Violation: repeat of the above problems is a workflow error; correct before considering HandsOff complete.
